<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-03T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-03T22:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/1004: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-03T22:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                            1922—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 4—9:40
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>67. Your telegram number 53, August 1, 3 p.m. The Peruvian Government
                                is of the opinion that the complementary act should be ratified and
                                ratifications exchanged in the same manner as the protocol itself,
                                of which it is an integral part according to its wording.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>